INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (84, 2, '2008-01-21 23:23:29', '2008-01-21 21:23:29', '<p>If you visited the site recently, you might have noticed some strange behaviour. Nothing to be alarmed about, I\'m just updating the new design. Hence, I won\'t be posting a new comic this week.</p><p>If you come across any bugs, don\'t hesitate to tell me or send a screenshot. I\'d be much obliged.</p>', 'New design', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-design', '', '', '2008-01-21 23:23:29', '2008-01-21 21:23:29', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/mic/2008/01/21/new-design/', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (87, 2, '2008-01-28 23:04:07', '2008-01-28 21:04:07', '<p>I felt like doing a bit of papercraft this weekend, so I made the comicversion of myself. Hope you like it.<br />\nIf you\'d like to assemble them yourself, you can download the pdf\'s of the models right here:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.mindbase21.be/downloads/papercraft/another_me-A.pdf" target="_blank">Another me, v.A</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.mindbase21.be/downloads/papercraft/another_me-B.pdf" target="_blank">Another me, v.B</a></p>', 'Another me: papercraft models', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'another-me-papercraft-models-2', '', '', '2008-01-28 23:04:07', '2008-01-28 21:04:07', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/mic/2008/01/28/another-me-papercraft-models-2/', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (94, 2, '2008-03-11 14:53:28', '2008-03-11 12:53:28', '<p>I know, I know, my comic-updates have been rather erratic so far. But we\'re in for a change, you and I. Since I\'m very much a list-person, I decided to finally add these updates as a "to-do" on my calendar.  Of course that doesn\'t mean much to you. It\'s not like there\'s someone standing behind me with a baseball bat to keep me in line, right? However, I have every intent at keeping to my list. I\'m starting off easy with a bi-weekly update. Something I\'ve been doing for the last couple of months anyway. And as a back-up, for when I\'m on vacation, or otherwise unable to post, I\'ll make sure to let you guys know (including a slacker-image).</p>\n<p>So, keep an eye on the site, and give a shout (profanity allowed) if I were to forget. </p>\n<p><strong>Updates will be every other Wednesdaynight, CET+1, </strong>starting this week.</p>', 'Update schedule', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'update-schedule', '', '', '2008-03-11 14:53:28', '2008-03-11 12:53:28', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/mic/2008/03/11/update-schedule/', 0, 'post', '', 1); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (105, 2, '2008-04-24 19:39:33', '2008-04-24 17:39:33', '<p>I live in a place where people are lucky enough to have descent social security and medical/dental work is affordable. So from this privileged position, I\'d like to help a fellow artist in need. Rachel needs to have heavy dental work done and it will costs her a fortune. Check out her site and donate something. There\'s some fun insentives as well.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.subcultureofone.com/teeth/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.subcultureofone.com/teeth/links/rachelwonkymouth468x60.jpg" alt="Fix Rachel\'s Wonky Mouth" /></a></p>', 'Help a comicker in need', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'help-a-comicker-in-need', '', '', '2008-04-24 19:39:33', '2008-04-24 17:39:33', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/mic/2008/04/24/help-a-comicker-in-need/', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (152, 2, '2008-12-01 23:38:24', '2008-12-01 22:38:24', '<p>If you read the comic ‘<a href="http://www.little-gamers.com/" target="_blank">Little Gamers</a>’ every once in a while, you may have noticed it\'s their 8th year birthday this week. And because Madsen is <a href="http://www.little-gamers.com/2008/12/01/8-years/"  target="_blank">a lazy bum</a>, they\'re running guestcomics all week. Including one by me on Saturday.<br />\nSo, you know, read ‘<a href="http://www.little-gamers.com/"  target="_blank">Little Gamers</a>’ this Saturday and come back here to tell me what you think of the comic.<br />\nDon\'t worry, I\'ll remind you all of it on Saturday as well.</p>\n<p>On another note, I\'m reading ‘How to make webcomics’, by the guys from Halfpixel (that being the guys behind <a href="http://www.pvponline.com"  target="_blank">PVP</a>, <a href="http://sheldoncomics.com"  target="_blank">Sheldon</a>, <a href="http://www.evil-comic.com/"  target="_blank">Evil Inc.</a> and <a href="http://www.starslipcrisis.com/"  target="_blank">Starslipcrisis</a>). Despite its 195 pages, it reads fast. Mostly because the type is large and there\'s lot\'s of strips &#038; examples inbetween text.<br />\nThe layout is a little chaotic though. Lots of extra blocks with tips and explanations crossing the normal flow of the chapters. It throws me off sometimes and I lose focus off what I\'m actually reading.<br />\nBut forgetting that, I\'m halfway through and I find it quite an interesting book.  They cover the \'making of\' from tips on character-development, through writing, to getting it online and building your audience. I haven\'t gotten to the branding and monetizing part yet, but it looks promising.<br />\nLike they say in the introduction: most of this is common sense and so you\'ll pick up the bits you hadn\'t thought of before and throw away the rest. These guys speak from experience so you (me?) will have a headstart and know what you\'re getting into. that\'s probably the best way to view it, not as a step-by-step manual but as a guide. With that in mind, it\'s an interesting read for anyone interested in webcomics and setting up an online business with creative work in mind.</p>\n<p>Cheers all.</p>', 'On making webcomics', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'guestcomic-2', '', '', '2008-12-01 23:38:24', '2008-12-01 22:38:24', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/mic/?p=152', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (160, 2, '2008-12-04 23:12:54', '2008-12-04 22:12:54', '<p>I decided to push my update schedule a bit. For the longest time I updated sporadically, then settled on 1 comic every 2 weeks. Which is sad, sad, sad. Still better than Dresden Codak*, but still… So starting now, I\'ll be <strong>posting weekly on Wednesday evening</strong> and maybe build a buffer in case of emergencies? yeah, I need that. If that goes well, and my writing improves, I can build it upwards from there.</p>\n<p>As I mentioned in the last blogpost, I was reading ‘How to make webcomics’ and the book inspired me. Despite the title, it\'s not an obnoxious \'this is how you do it\' manual but a nice guide. Like having a heart-to-heart with you\'re favorite family-member about the important things in life. Anyway, that\'s how it feels to me.<br />\n I\'ve been struggling with my creative side and what career (if any) I want to build for myself. This, to those who know me, doesn\'t come as a surprise. Doubt is a big constant in my life. But what I do know is that I like drawing and from the multitude of areas where one use this skill, comics is the most important one to me. So it would be a shame to just let it slip. It\'s good excercise.</p>\n<p>* don\'t shoot me, I\'m actually a big fan of Dresden Codac</p>', 'News on Updates', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'news-on-updates', '', '', '2008-12-04 23:12:54', '2008-12-04 22:12:54', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/comics/?p=160', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (168, 2, '2008-12-06 13:26:22', '2008-12-06 12:26:22', '<p>Welcome to the people coming in from Little Gamers! I noticed a 175% increase in visitors since they linked me in their post about guestcomics, so thanks for dropping by. It\'s always nice to see new people.<br />\nSo hey, I have a guestcomic <a href="http://www.little-gamers.com/2008/12/06/guestcomics-2/" target="_blank">on Little Gamers</a> today. <a href="http://www.little-gamers.com/2008/12/06/guestcomics-2/" target="_blank">Go check it out</a></p>', 'Guestcomics: Little Gamers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'guestcomics-little-gamers', '', '', '2008-12-06 13:26:22', '2008-12-06 12:26:22', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/comics/?p=168', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
