INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (361, 2, '2009-06-29 22:29:20', '2009-06-29 20:29:20', '<a href="http://store.tnppress.com/mci-shop/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.mindbase21.be/comics/wp-content/themes/comicpress-0903/images/teaser-shop.png" alt="shop" title="shop"></a>\n\nThe new TNP shop launched last week, so I\'ve put up a little teaser in the right-sidebar for you to click and get some goodies. It\'s buttons for now, and I\'ll think about adding some tshirts later on.\n<a href="http://mindbase21.etsy.com/">My Etsy store</a> will continue to carry all handmade items, like the dolls.', 'Attention all shoppers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'attention-all-shoppers', '', '', '2009-06-29 22:29:20', '2009-06-29 20:29:20', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/comics/?p=361', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (366, 2, '2009-07-04 15:56:28', '2009-07-04 13:56:28', 'I just made a facebook Page for ‘My Chronic Insomnia’ and so I’ll dissolve the old Group in favour of this new Page. Obviously I expect the horde of fans to follow me there and become a fan of <a target="_blank" href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/My-Chronic-Insomnia/99008995821">My Chronic Insomnia on Facebook.</a>\nNow If you’ll excuse me, I’m going to face the heatwave outside and try to find something to drink before I passout.', 'Facebooking', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'facebooking', '', '', '2009-07-04 15:56:28', '2009-07-04 13:56:28', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/comics/?p=366', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (371, 2, '2009-07-19 14:53:35', '2009-07-19 12:53:35', 'An overview of what’s been going on lately. Some I already mentioned in passing when updating comics, but really it makes more sense to group it into a post.\n<ul><li>As you all know, I’m sure, we’ve got <a href="http://forums.tnppress.com" target="_blank">an awesome forum</a> at TNP Press where you can share your thoughts on everything from antlers to zootropes (link in the navigation bar). And now every comic got it’s own special forum.  Including <a href="http://forums.tnppress.com/viewforum.php?f=41" target="_blank">My Chronic Insomnia!</a> <a href="http://forums.tnppress.com/viewforum.php?f=41" target="_blank">Go forth and post</a> thy twisted thoughts and share opinions with likeminded individuals!</li><li>If you’re on Facebook (like all the cool kids and the hip elderly), become a fan of <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/My-Chronic-Insomnia/99008995821" target="_blank">the MCI Fanpage</a>. <br />On twitter, you can now follow <a href="http://www.twitter.com/mci_comics" target="_blank">@mci_comics</a> for news and updates on the comic.</li><li>I’m working on a whole new website and online identity. Not just the comic site, but my whole portfolio will get a make-over this summer. I want it to be more profesional, memorable and creative than ‘mindbase21’. Especially for new people to come visit and explore. </li><li>Lastly, the obligatory sales-pitch (it pays for my hosting): get your awesome buttons <a href="http://store.tnppress.com/mci-shop/" target="_blank">in the shop</a>. 5 buttons for $7, that includes shipping.</li>', 'Updates', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'updates', '', '', '2009-07-19 14:53:35', '2009-07-19 12:53:35', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/comics/?p=371', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (384, 2, '2009-07-26 23:00:59', '2009-07-26 21:00:59', 'Oh, I know what you\'re thinking:<em> “Didn\'t you just get fired? You must have plenty of time!” “And don’t you make a weekly comic anyway? That’s 7 days to finish 6 panels, you lazy bastard!”</em>\n\nHey now! That’s very insensitive of you! I’m in a fragile state right now and I might start crying! Alas, I\'m not leaving The Job until October and I\'m in the middle of other exciting creative things at the moment! Including packing to move to another apartment soon.\n\nSo some <strong>guestcomics or pinups</strong> would really come in handy. You can post a reply and I\'ll give you my e-mail address if you’re interested.\nI\'d like to have a first piece to post by<strong> Tuesday, August 4th</strong> <em>–So close by, I’m very sorry–</em> but you can keep sending stuff in <strong>until August 25th</strong> to have the month covered.\nInternet fame awaits you, don\'t be shy!', 'Calling guest artists', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'calling-guest-artists', '', '', '2009-07-26 23:00:59', '2009-07-26 21:00:59', '', 0, 'http://www.mindbase21.be/comics/?p=384', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (422, 2, '2009-09-16 16:01:09', '2009-09-16 14:01:09', 'I present to you: a new design and a new name. The comic has officially moved and I hope to keep the new name for a while. So don\'t forget to update your bookmarks and RSS subscription!\r\nI chose Beardfluff because it sounds fun and lighthearted to me. If there\'s one thing I try to do here, it\'s not taking myself too seriously. Of course, there\'s still room for that blackened, sarcastic and cynical part of my soul in here. That\'s what makes this all the more fun.\r\nBesides the comics, this\'ll be the place where I put my other drawings and various craft-related things. It\'s still a bit empty on that front, and you might encounter some bugs while I\'m still cleaning up the place.\r\nFeel free to comment on the changes and share your opinion on the new site!', 'Moving to Beardfluff', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beardfluff', '', '', '2009-09-16 16:02:13', '2009-09-16 14:02:13', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=422', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (434, 2, '2009-09-26 16:36:35', '2009-09-26 14:36:35', 'Because of the recent move of the comic, I decided to set up new adboxes. I removed 1 skyscraper in favour of a square and some buttons. That way I save some space and give some more options. With any luck, these ads will pay for the hosting. So if someone\'s interested in running ads, be sure to click the PW link under the adbox of your choice.\r\nThanks, and happy bidding!', 'Advertising on Beardfluff.com', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'advertising-on-beardfluff-com', '', '', '2009-10-01 20:54:52', '2009-10-01 18:54:52', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=434', 0, 'post', '', 2); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (584, 2, '2009-10-30 03:00:55', '2009-10-30 01:00:55', 'Hello folks. As you’ve no doubt noticed, the store has been offline for quite a while (mainly because of server issues). But those dark days are over, my friends! Following the trend of other comickers (comicers?) out there, I\'ve set up shop over at <a href="http://beardfluff.bigcartel.com" target="_blank">Bigcartel</a>. (link in the left sidebar, just click the Shop image)\r\nSo far, it’s just the button packs in the products list, but there’s more to come. See you in the store!', 'New store', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-store', '', '', '2009-10-30 03:00:55', '2009-10-30 01:00:55', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=584', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (589, 2, '2009-11-09 19:18:51', '2009-11-09 19:18:51', 'I’ve had some fun drawing with my old Pentel brush pen lately. Just added a couple of drawings to the <a href="http://beardfluff.com/art/sketchbook">sketchbook</a> section. The girl with the mallet is Ramona Flowers, from Brian Lee O’Malley\'s “Scott Pilgrim” and the screaming dude comes from Dragonball Z.\r\n<p><a rel="lightbox[]" href=\'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/wp-content/gallery/sketchbook/brush_ramona.png\' title=\'Ramona sketch, Ramona © Brian Lee O’Malley of ‘Scott Pilgrim’ fame\'><img src=\'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/wp-content/gallery/sketchbook/thumbs/thumbs_brush_ramona.png\' alt=\'brush_ramona\' class=\'ngg-singlepic ngg-left\' /></a><a rel="lightbox[]" href=\'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/wp-content/gallery/sketchbook/brush_girl.png\' title=\'manga-ish girl\'><img src=\'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/wp-content/gallery/sketchbook/thumbs/thumbs_brush_girl.png\' alt=\'brush_girl\' class=\'ngg-singlepic ngg-left\' /></a><a rel="lightbox[]" href=\'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/wp-content/gallery/sketchbook/brush_dragonballz.png\' title=\'Dragonball Z fan sketch\'><img src=\'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/wp-content/gallery/sketchbook/thumbs/thumbs_brush_dragonballz.png\' alt=\'brush_dragonballz\' class=\'ngg-singlepic ngg-left\' /></a>\r\n<div class="clear"></div></p>', 'Brush drawings', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'brush-drawings', '', '', '2009-11-09 19:20:52', '2009-11-09 19:20:52', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=589', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (602, 2, '2009-11-13 13:43:19', '2009-11-13 13:43:19', '<a href="http://paperblackninja.com/downloads/holiday-cards/"><img style="margin-right:5px" alt="" src="http://www.paperblackninja.com/media/eindejaar_spirits_tn.png" title="Spirits" class="alignleft" width="100" height="150" /></a> The season for giving and feeling sorry for ourselves is almost upon us. That’s why I made a couple of <a href="http://www.paperblackninja.com/downloads/holiday-cards/">alternative Holiday Cards</a>. They are free for you to give to unsuspecting friends and enemies alike. They come in a handy .pdf (for printing) and .png (to send online).\r\nIf you saw <a href="http://www.paperblackninja.com/downloads/valentinesdaycards/">the Valentine’s Day cards</a> I made, you know what to expect.\r\nEnjoy!', 'Holiday cards', '<a href="http://paperblackninja.com/downloads/holiday-cards/"><img style="margin-right:5px" alt="" src="http://www.paperblackninja.com/media/eindejaar_spirits_tn.png" title="Spirits" class="alignleft" width="100" height="150" /></a> The season for giving and feeling sorry for ourselves is almost upon us. That’s why I made…', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'holiday-cards', '', '', '2009-12-24 13:55:56', '2009-12-24 13:55:56', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=602', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (729, 2, '2009-11-20 11:18:53', '2009-11-20 11:18:53', 'The month is almost over and I still haven\'t talked about <a href="http://www.movember.com/" target="_blank">Movember</a>, shame on me. So, next comic will be dedicated to that. What the heck is Movember, you ask? In short: it’s all about growing a moustache during November, to help raise money for prostate cancer awareness. Check out the previous link for more info, and check out <a href="http://ryanpeq.livejournal.com/171459.html" target="_blank">awesome cartoonist Ryan\'s moustache</a> to see a fine example.\r\n\r\nIn extra extra special news: my good buddy and TNP collegue Joenis made <a href="http://unconsciousink.com/inklings/beard-fluff/" target="_blank">Beardfluff fan art</a>! It’s fantastic and you should all bookmark his site. There, I said it, no taking it back now!', 'Movember and fan art', 'The month is almost over and I still haven\'t talked about <a href="http://www.movember.com/" target="_blank">Movember</a>, shame on me.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'movember-and-fan-art', '', '', '2009-11-26 17:07:09', '2009-11-26 17:07:09', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=729', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (775, 2, '2009-11-26 16:47:44', '2009-11-26 16:47:44', 'Beardfluff v.2.0 has just gone live and I hope it is to you liking. Most radical change is the structure of the homepage. I really wanted this site to be about more then just showing a comic and be done with it. Of course comics are still the focal point of Beardfluff but it’s also the place where I put my sketches and illustrations. So those two got their own little window, along with the news so you can instantly see what’s going on. Below that, a variety of links related to the comic (category navigation, contact and social media stuff, commercial links). For example, there’s now a handy little tab to direct you to<a href="http://chat.tnppress.com" target="_blank"> the TNP Chatroom</a> where you can ask questions or just sociallize with the artists.\r\n\r\nFor structure and concept, I took a bit of inspiration from various other webcomics, like <a href="http://www.dresdencodak.com" target="_blank">Dresden Codak </a>who in my opinion has one of the best designed webcomic sites right now. I may not be the most stunning visually, but everything you need in on there in a clear and approachable way and what you don’t need is disposed off. Best of all, it stays clear of that out-of-the-box ComicPress look that 90% of webcomics have. No offense towards Comicpress – they did a great job making it easy for creators to put up a webcomics – but I’m sick of the uniformity. Most people will change the colors and add a few illustrations but they won’t have an overall concept for the site. More often than not, it’s a question of webdesign skill of course. I don’t expect every artist to be a designer and developer. And I have my tastes as well. I’ve got a thing for the practical and ‘less’ mentality when it comes to sites.\r\nSome other nice examples: <a href="http://pvponline.com">PvP Online</a>, <a href="http://pajamaforest.com/" target="_blank">Pajama Forest</a> and <a href="http://www.octopuspie.com/" target="_blank">Octopus Pie</a>\r\n\r\nThe design stays close to the previous version (colors and some visual elements) but also refers to my other site, <a href="http://paperblackninja.com" target="_blank">PaperblackNinja</a> which focuses more on design and acts as my professional portfolio. I felt that since these are 2 aspects of myself that are closely related anyway, I might as well show it in the design as well.\r\n \r\nNo doubt I’ll be cursing at this redesign by this time next week, since I’m never happy with anything that comes out of these hands, but for now I’m satisfied with what I’ve made. Let me know if anything’s broken because their might still be a couple of bugs and oversights. And if you’re watching this on IE6, you’re trying too hard.\r\n\r\nCheers!', 'Redesign', 'Beardfluff v.2.0 has just gone live and I hope it is to you liking. Most radical change is the structure of …', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'redesign', '', '', '2009-11-26 17:07:36', '2009-11-26 17:07:36', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=775', 0, 'post', '', 6); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (840, 2, '2009-12-24 13:56:35', '2009-12-24 13:56:35', 'I don\'t really have a Christmas or New Year or related holiday comic, but in any case, I hope you have a great time! I plan to eat until I pass out, as is tradition. To get the party started, I\'ll leave you with the wise words of the great Roy Zimmerman.\r\n\r\nCheers!\r\n\r\n<object width="350" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/oRkdErudb_8&hl=nl_NL&fs=1&"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/oRkdErudb_8&hl=nl_NL&fs=1&" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="350" height="344"></embed></object>\r\n\r\nAnd in case you haven\'t yet, you can still get your\r\n <a href="http://www.paperblackninja.com/downloads/holiday-cards/"> free holiday cards</a>.', 'Happy Christma-Hanu-Rama-Ka-Dona-Kwanzaa!', 'I don\'t really have a Christmas or New Year or related holiday comic, but in any case, I hope you have a great time! I plan to eat until I pass out, as is tradition. To get the party started, I\'ll leave you with the wise words of …', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'happy-christma-hanu-rama-ka-dona-kwanzaa', '', '', '2010-01-12 19:49:05', '2010-01-12 19:49:05', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=840', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (898, 2, '2010-03-11 21:59:24', '2010-03-11 20:59:24', 'I recently made the call on Twitter, but I\'ll say it here again. In April, I\'d like to take a bit of time off, so I could use some guest art to fill the blanks in my update schedule.\r\nThe only requirement is that the comics or art should be a <strong>maximum of 800px wide</strong>. It can be less if you want. Of course I\'ll be crediting & linking you in the post. If you need a guestcomic from me in the future, I\'ll be happy to help.\r\nSubmissions are open from now <strong>until the end of April.</strong> You can contact me via <a href="http://www.twitter.com/paperblackninja">Twitter</a> or <a href="mailto:rembrand(at)paperblackninja(dot)com">mail me</a>.\r\nSpread the word!', 'Open call for guest comics and art', 'I recently made the call on Twitter, but I\'ll say it here again. In April, I\'d like to take a bit of time off, so I could use some guest art …', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'open-call-for-guest-comics-and-art', '', '', '2010-03-11 22:04:54', '2010-03-11 21:04:54', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=898', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (939, 2, '2010-04-06 21:43:26', '2010-04-06 19:43:26', 'Okay, so it\'s about time we had a Fanpage for Beardfluff that was actually called ‘Beardfluff I think. And what better time to make one, then the present. I’ve also taken the opportunity to clean up the site somewhat and add a new logo/icon in the header. Let me know what you think about it.\r\n\r\nSo here\'s the deal:\r\n- become a fan of the Page before April 14th 2010 and comment or \'like\' the first post. (There\'s only 1 post so it’s really easy)\r\n- On Wednesday the 14th, I will pick 3 people at random who will receive 1) a set of 5 buttons and 2) a drawing of a most amazing beard.\r\n\r\nSound good? Then head over to the new page, become a fan and comment/‘like’ it!\r\n\r\n<a target="_blank" href="http://www.facebook.com/Beardfluff">http://www.facebook.com/Beardfluff</a>', 'Win stuff! Become a fan of the new Beardfluff Facebook Page ', 'Okay, so it’s about time we had a Fanpage for Beardfluff that was actually called ‘Beardfluff I think. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'win-stuff-become-a-fan-of-the-new-beardfluff-facebook-page', '', '', '2010-05-15 23:49:04', '2010-05-15 21:49:04', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=939', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (964, 2, '2010-04-24 15:35:04', '2010-04-24 13:35:04', 'A while back I was contacted by Knut of the <a target="_blank" href="http://www.eardrumsmusic.com">Eardrums Music blog</a> and <a target="_blank" href="http://www.eardrumspop.com">Eardrums Pop</a> (the label). He was looking for people to contribute comics for the booklet of a new music collection.  After a long wait, <strong>Between the Waves</strong> is finally out for everyone to download and enjoy (for free!). It comes in 3 parts and the booklet is included with part A:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.eardrumspop.com/2010/04/19/b2wvola/">part A</a></li>\r\n<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.eardrumspop.com/2010/04/19/b2wvolb/">part B</a></li>\r\n<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.eardrumspop.com/2010/04/19/b2wvolc/">part C</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>Between the waves</strong> features a comic about ‘The Greatest Beard’ and it turns out Philippa Rice of <a target="_blank" href="http://www.mycardboardlife.com">My Cardboard Life</a> also made one. The whole book is bloody brilliant, from design to content really. Plenty of info on all the bands/musicians and even poetry. So be sure to <a target="_blank" href="http://www.eardrumspop.com/2010/04/19/b2wvola/">check it out</a>.', 'Between the waves', 'A while back I was contacted by Knut of the Eardrums Music  …', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'between-the-waves', '', '', '2010-04-24 15:47:09', '2010-04-24 13:47:09', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=964', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
