INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1423, 2, '2011-01-05 07:50:53', '2011-01-05 06:50:53', 'Man, those resolutions never amount to anything so I just stop making them altogether. I’m serious about the drawing though but I already started last month. The goal is to fill a page in my sketchbook a day (when I’m not drawing the comic).\r\n\r\n<strong>I do have a few changes lined up:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maybe you noticed <strong>the brand new font</strong> (thanks <a href="http://www.comicbookfonts.com/">Comic Book Fonts</a> for the New Year’s discount!). The uppercase letters and the lack of special characters in ‘Anime Ace’ bothered me a bit so I’m trying this font called ‘Comicrazy’ now.\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>I added my <a href="http://beardfluff.bigcartel.com/product/cut-out-moustaches">cut-out moustaches in the store</a> and the beards now come in <a href="http://beardfluff.bigcartel.com/product/cut-out-beard">4 different colours</a>.\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Ah, and I’m currently working on the <strong>new site design</strong>, which should be finished sometime in Februari I think.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSo what are you up to this year?', 'Some resolutions', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'some-resolutions', '', '', '2011-01-21 21:20:07', '2011-01-21 20:20:07', '', 0, 'http://beardfluff.com/?post_type=webcomic_post&p=1423', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 4); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1431, 2, '2011-01-12 07:50:34', '2011-01-12 06:50:34', 'That’s right, time for another question for Beard. Remember, you can always ask your own questions on the <a href="http://www.formspring.me/Beardfluff">Beardfluff Formspring</a> or on <a href="http://twitter.com/beardfluff">Twitter</a>. Against my better judgement, I’ve given Beard full control of<a href="http://twitter.com/beardfluff"> the Beardfluff Twitter account</a>.\r\nHow do you like his new look, by the way? Is he rocking that moustache or what?\r\n\r\nA small note about the comic: if you haven’t heard of <a href="http://www.taramcpherson.com/">Tara McPherson</a>, I’m sure you’ve seen some of her artwork around. She’s created some <a href="http://www.taramcpherson.com/art/Paintings/Lost%20Constellations">very recognizable characters</a>. The comic doesn’t really have the best likeness I’m affraid, sorry about that. (Reference picture from <a href="http://lululovesmakingthings.blogspot.com/2009/08/tara-mcpherson.html">Lulu</a>)', 'Question time 2', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'question-time-2', '', '', '2011-01-10 21:10:51', '2011-01-10 20:10:51', '', 0, 'http://beardfluff.com/?post_type=webcomic_post&p=1431', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 2); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1433, 2, '2011-01-19 07:50:29', '2011-01-19 06:50:29', 'It’s <a href="http://bearduary.com/" rel="external">Bearduary</a>! Grow a beard, maybe try out a new style, send them pictures. Or not, you know, whatever. In any case, I’m having fun with the Beard comics lately so I think I’ll keep it going for a bit longer.', 'The many styles of Beard', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-many-styles-of-beard', '', '', '2011-01-19 07:57:34', '2011-01-19 06:57:34', '', 0, 'http://beardfluff.com/?post_type=webcomic_post&p=1433', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 2); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1438, 2, '2011-01-26 07:50:16', '2011-01-26 06:50:16', 'No real comic today I’m affraid. I’ve been spending way too much energy on this site-redesign. I hope you enjoy these early valentines instead though. I won’t have any printed cards in the shop but you’re free to to download and send the digital versions if you want: <a href="http://beardfluff.com/wp-content/webcomic/misc/valentine-batman-web.jpg">Batman</a>, <a href="http://beardfluff.com/wp-content/webcomic/misc/valentine-bear-web.jpg">Bear</a>, <a href="http://beardfluff.com/wp-content/webcomic/misc/valentine-moustache-web.jpg">Moustache rides</a>\r\n\r\nI’m heading off to Germany tomorrow so next week I’ll have some <strong>guest-art</strong> for you by a nice chap from Brazil. By the way, if you ever feel the urge to share some guest art or a comic, you’re most welcome to <a href="mailto:rembrand(at)beardfluff(dot)com">email me</a>. I don’t have any other guest-post scheduled for the moment but you knever know. I’ll probably do another guest-week later in the year as well.', 'Valentines 2011', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'valentines-2011', '', '', '2011-02-09 18:28:49', '2011-02-09 17:28:49', '', 0, 'http://beardfluff.com/?post_type=webcomic_post&p=1438', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 2); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1445, 2, '2011-02-02 07:50:22', '2011-02-02 06:50:22', 'Here’s some guest art for you today, since I spent most of last week in Frankfurt instead of making comics.\r\n\r\nThese wicked drawings were made by Brazilian underground artist <a href="http://www.arthurdoomer.com/" rel="external">Doomer</a>. He’s into dirty punk and death metal and has a thing for skulls but don’t let that scare you off, he\'s a pretty nice guy. The work gets pretty heavy and morbid sometimes but anyone who diggs R. Crumb, Francis Bacon, M.C. Escher ànd Will Eisner is definitely okay in my book.\r\n\r\nYou can check out more of his stuff on <a href="http://www.arthurdoomer.com/" rel="external">arthurdoomer.com</a> or on <a href="http://arthurdoomer.blogspot.com/">his blog</a> (updates daily). He’s also making stuff for magazines and bands, so if you’re in need of a band logo, <a href="http://www.arthurdoomer.com/doomer_pages/doomer_english_home.html">he’s the guy to call</a>.', 'guest art - Doomer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'guest-art-doomer', '', '', '2011-02-09 18:32:09', '2011-02-09 17:32:09', '', 0, 'http://beardfluff.com/?post_type=webcomic_post&p=1445', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1451, 2, '2011-02-09 07:50:31', '2011-02-09 06:50:31', 'A couple weeks ago I went to the great city of Frankfurt-Am-Main with a couple of friends. Fun times were had by all. We stayed at a hostel in the red light district (which was okay really), met an energetic Australian (aren’t they all?), saw the sights and visited a couple museums. My favourite was the Museum of Natural History, where this conversation took place. Thanks for the dialogue, Brecht!', 'Natural history', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'natural-history', '', '', '2011-02-09 23:21:38', '2011-02-09 22:21:38', '', 0, 'http://beardfluff.com/?post_type=webcomic_post&p=1451', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1465, 2, '2011-02-16 07:00:37', '2011-02-16 06:00:37', 'The viking is based on my friend Efey’s man. She asked for a comic and promptly triggered the idea by pointing out his beard looks on fire lately. So I couldn’t pass up on that. ', 'Red beard', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'red-beard', '', '', '2011-02-15 19:09:30', '2011-02-15 18:09:30', '', 0, 'http://beardfluff.com/?post_type=webcomic_post&p=1465', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0);
